<section id="scheme2">
    <h2>Education and Career Development Loan</h2>
    <p>The Education and Career Development Loan aims to empower women by providing financial assistance for education and career advancement.</p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Low-interest loans specifically for women pursuing education or career development</li>
        <li>Coverage for tuition fees, training programs, and certification courses</li>
        <li>Flexible repayment options to suit individual financial situations</li>
        <li>Access to resources and support for skill enhancement and career progression</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This loan scheme enables women to invest in their education and skills, helping them unlock new opportunities and achieve their professional goals. Whether it's pursuing higher education, acquiring specialized training, or obtaining certifications, the Education and Career Development Loan provides the necessary financial support for women to advance in their chosen fields.</p>
<a href="apply3.jsp" class="apply-button">Apply Now</a>

</section>
<section id="scheme3">
    <h2>Women in Agriculture Loan Scheme</h2>
    <p>The Women in Agriculture Loan Scheme aims to support and empower women involved in agricultural activities.</p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Specialized loans designed for women in agriculture</li>
        <li>Financial assistance for purchasing land, equipment, seeds, and livestock</li>
        <li>Training programs on sustainable farming practices and modern agricultural techniques</li>
        <li>Access to market information and opportunities</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This loan scheme recognizes the vital role that women play in agriculture and offers the necessary financial resources and knowledge to help them thrive in the sector. Whether it's starting a new agricultural venture or expanding an existing one, the Women in Agriculture Loan Scheme provides support to women farmers and cultivators, promoting their economic empowerment and contributing to the growth of the agricultural sector.</p>
